sql:
SELECT user_id
FROM trips
WHERE distance = (SELECT MAX(distance) FROM trips);

SELECT mode, AVG(average_speed) AS avg_speed
FROM trips
GROUP BY mode;

external_knowledge:
- "wanderer" refers to users;
- "roamed" refers to traveled;
- "paths" are the different modes of transportation (walking, driving, cycling);
- "favored route" indicates the mode with the highest report count.

- "shedding light on their identity" refers to identifying users by their user ID and name;
- "sum of their contributions" alludes to the total amount paid by users;
- "fruits of their documented endeavors" metaphorically represents the number of reports they have generated.
